Start Python in Windows
1. Check installed versions
python --version
py -0

2. Run default Python
python

This runs the version registered in your system PATH.
In my case: 3.13.12

3. Run via Python Launcher
py

This runs the default version configured in the Python Launcher.
In your case: 3.14.3

4. Run a specific Python version
py -3.13
py -3.14

5. Run a Python file
python main.py
py main.py
py -3.14 main.py


Notepad++ → Run Cheat Sheet
1. Run a Python file

Go to: Run → Run…
Insert:  cmd /k py -3.14 "$(FULL_CURRENT_PATH)"

Or if you want to use the PATH version:
cmd /k python "$(FULL_CURRENT_PATH)"


2. Run Node.js file
cmd /k node "$(FULL_CURRENT_PATH)"


3. What the variables mean

$(FULL_CURRENT_PATH) – full path to the current file
$(CURRENT_DIRECTORY) – current working directory
$(FILE_NAME) – file name only


4. Change directory first, then run
cmd /k cd "$(CURRENT_DIRECTORY)" && py -3.14 "$(FILE_NAME)"


Quick Rules

python – version from PATH
py – Python version launcher
cmd /k – execute and keep console open
cmd /c – execute and close console
